default1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultGlobal progress with CCS has been slow compared to estimates by national governments and inter-governmental bodies. Nevertheless, Bloomberg New 
defaultEnergy Finance data show that public and private organisations have channelled $26.8bn into CCS commercialisation since 2000. Government grants make up 54% of that total. 
default&#xa0;
default2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultGlobal investment in projects has remained steady since 2009 at around $2.8bn a ye
defaultar (BNEF, 7 March 2013). That investment has produced seventeen medium- to-large CCS projects operating, or under construction, with another 55 at the planning stage (GCCSI).
default&#xa0;
default3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe UK is one of the leading countries in terms of developing an effective CCS 
defaultpolicy framework, despite slow progress with its attempts to fund demonstration projects (2006-11).  A new approach has emerged in the form of the CCS Commercialisation Programme and the Electricity Market Reform (EMR). This has the potential to match UK C
defaultCS rhetoric and delivery on the ground.   
default&#xa0;
default4.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultDECC’s Commercialisation Programme has selected two projects – White Rose and Peterhead - to enter negotiations for Front-End Engineering and Design (FEED) studies, with a view to making final investment decisio
defaultns in 2015.
default&#xa0;
default5.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWhite Rose is a cost effective, realistic and deliverable project, which offers an excellent opportunity to establish the commercial future of the technology. The project is 
defaultEurope’s only CCS project being considered for NER300 funding
default (for f
defaulturther details on the project see the attached slide pack.) 
default&#xa0;
default6.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIt is essential that the momentum is maintained in the Commercialisation Programme, so that two projects can enter operation in the 2018-2020 timeframe
default. 
defaultAs the Committee on Climate Change has said: 
default&#xa0;
default‘It will be important that the Government continues to learn the lessons of the earlier failed CCS Competition, including the need for rapid progress and avoiding traditional procurement processes unsuited to
default a complex first-of-a-kind project.’ 
default(CCC Carbon Budget Progress Report 2013.)
default&#xa0;
default7.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe strongly agree with that view, in particular the need for Government to take a more innovative and collaborative approach, rather than relying on a traditional procurement 
defaultmodel. 
default&#xa0;
